}}","type":"string"}]},"options":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.set","typeVersion":3.4,"position":[5157,1420],"id":"97405e2a-b76a-4c39-93a5-592e959ae1ee","name":"Capture Failure Context"},{"parameters":{"select":"channel","channelId":{"__rl":true,"mode":"name","value":"#ai-ops","cachedResultName":"#ai-ops"},"text":"=🚨 {{ $json.workflow }} failed at {{ $json.failedNode }}: {{ $json.errorMessage }}","otherOptions":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.slack","typeVersion":2.3,"position":[5481,1420],"id":"fc06e96a-21fc-47fa-aaa9-7391f900cfff","name":"Escalate Failure to Slack","retryOnFail":true,"maxTries":3,"waitBetweenTries":2000},{"parameters":{"content":"### Receive Inbound Webhook\n\nEntry point: listens for POST calls on `/wf00887-request`. Use the TEST url while building, switch callers to the PRODUCTION url after publishing.\n\nNext: Required Fields Present?","width":280,"height":232,"color":5},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-330,520],"id":"b38bcf1e-2e8a-572e-90f7-7f1d42880691","name":"Note: Receive Inbound Webhook"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Required Fields Present?\n\nTwo-way gate on `={{ $json.query }}`. TRUE continues the happy path, FALSE takes the alternate branch.\n\nPorts: ①→ Detect Sentiment · ②→ Abort — Malformed Input","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-6,520],"id":"55c201f2-1dd4-0401-aad6-b17e2c0c206b","name":"Note: Required Fields Present?"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Abort — Malformed Input\n\nFails fast with a clear message; triggers the error workflow instead of processing bad data.","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-6,1030],"id":"31515fc6-86aa-86c7-eac2-9c2848c72ceb","name":"Note: Abort — Malformed Input"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Detect Sentiment\n\nScores the text's sentiment; ports fire positive / neutral / negative.\n\nPorts: ①→ Escalate Negative — Discord · ②→ Log Neutral Feedback, Capture Failure Context · ③→ Thank the Sender\n\n⚠ failures exit via the error rail","width":280,"height":232,"color":6},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[318,520],"id":"6a6c0b24-9ab8-d8db-0b0e-88f6bf174985","name":"Note: Detect Sentiment"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Google Gemini Chat Model\n\nChat model powering the AI step (model: `models/gemini-2.5-flash`). Swap providers here without rewiring.\n\nFeeds **Detect Sentiment** as `languageModel`\n\n🔑 Google AI API key","width":280,"height":232,"color":6},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[561,1090],"id":"38d31427-13e0-5bad-7fcb-f1109bc717a1","name":"Note: Google Gemini Chat Model"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Escalate Negative — Discord\n\ndiscord — `action` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Collect All Outcomes · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Discord webhook URL","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[885,40],"id":"cee3b778-00a3-920d-b5b3-42c5c29ed3f3","name":"Note: Escalate Negative — Discord"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Log Neutral Feedback\n\nnotion — `create` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Collect All Outcomes · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Notion integration token","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1209,520],"id":"15fd026e-6f56-3044-dafd-ff96c44e8ed8","name":"Note: Log Neutral Feedback"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Thank the Sender\n\nslack — `action` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Collect All Outcomes · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Slack OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1533,1000],"id":"1db7a08a-beb0-aafc-cd99-5d22ff3a3a01","name":"Note: Thank the Sender"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Collect All Outcomes\n\nRejoins 3 branches into one stream (mode: append) so downstream logic runs once.\n\nNext: Sort Requests Newest First","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[2505,520],"id":"092b4b64-73ba-db87-908f-1ad70826d5da","name":"Note: Collect All Outcomes"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Sort Requests Newest First\n\nOrders items (newest first) so limits and digests pick the most relevant records.\n\nNext: Guard Non-Empty query","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[3801,520],"id":"5b520fd9-dcdf-0275-13e2-11406c29d3a8","name":"Note: Sort Requests Newest First"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Guard Non-Empty query\n\nDrops items that fail the condition; only qualifying items continue (no false branch).\n\nNext: Cap Batch Volume","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4125,520],"id":"0830fac3-a995-cf67-97c3-8fe28cdf77a8","name":"Note: Guard Non-Empty query"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Cap Batch Volume\n\nCaps the stream at 50 items to protect downstream quotas.\n\nNext: Align Field Names","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4449,520],"id":"610f64e7-5429-3225-f37e-de22ac48d00f","name":"Note: Cap Batch Volume"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Align Field Names\n\nNormalizes field names so every source feeds the same downstream schema.\n\nNext: Summarize Run Stats","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4773,520],"id":"84a99fcd-8ada-1fa8-3b51-a9af13c0eecd","name":"Note: Align Field Names"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Summarize Run Stats\n\nShapes the item: writes `runAt`, `itemCount`, `status`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Append Audit Row (Notion)","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5097,520],"id":"7dee5d90-6423-aeb4-621d-620298a7641b","name":"Note: Summarize Run Stats"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Append Audit Row (Notion)\n\nnotion — `create` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Send Summary to Slack · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Notion integration token","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5421,520],"id":"a4f8ca68-6942-9545-0949-07adf9607cc6","name":"Note: Append Audit Row (Notion)"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Send Summary to Slack\n\nslack — `action` operation against the connected account.\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Slack OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5745,520],"id":"0e799ff9-f0bd-b422-fa3d-3d38da39a9e2","name":"Note: Send Summary to Slack"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Capture Failure Context\n\nShapes the item: writes `failedNode`, `errorMessage`, `workflow`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Escalate Failure to Slack","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5097,1540],"id":"98569067-d053-84ec-ea4f-b2e6effac521","name":"Note: Capture Failure Context"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Escalate Failure to Slack\n\nslack — `action` operation against the connected account.\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · 🔑 Slack OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5421,1540],"id":"141096c2-2c4c-cce3-1324-edfcca5920e1","name":"Note: Escalate Failure to Slack"},{"parameters":{"content":"# Digest documents with Notion and Discord without manual work\n\n**Pattern:** AI Summarize & Route · **Level:** Advanced · **Trigger:** Webhook\n\n## What it does\nDigest documents with Notion and Discord without manual work. It fires the moment an external system calls its webhook.\n\n## Why it exists\nManual task automation is slow and error-prone; this workflow makes the process repeatable, monitored and hands-off, with failures surfaced instead of silently lost.\n\n## Main flow\nReceive Inbound Webhook → Required Fields Present? → Detect Sentiment → Escalate Negative — Discord → Collect All Outcomes → Sort Requests Newest First → Guard Non-Empty query → …\n\n## Use it for\n- Teams that want to ai summarize & route without manual effort\n- Anyone automating task automation in ai\n- Replacing a fragile manual process with a reliable workflow\n\n## You get\n- Responds in seconds\n- Improves response time\n- Scales without extra headcount\n\n## Before first run\nConnect credentials: Discord webhook URL; Google AI API key; Notion integration token; Slack OAuth2.\nFollow the color key: 🟦 entry · 🟪 AI · 🟫 actions · ⬜ utilities · 🟩 outputs · 🟥 error rail.\nEach node has its own doc card underneath — read those before editing.","width":480,"height":900},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-830,80],"id":"2c17b70d-c121-6a10-669e-5243a1dfc281","name":"📘 Workflow Overview"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🛟 Error handling & retries\n\nExternal calls retry **3× with 2s backoff**. Anything still failing exits through its node's error output into the red error rail → context is captured and the on-call channel is alerted. Set an n8n **Error Workflow** in settings as the final safety net.","width":360,"height":260,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-230,-500],"id":"759f9b71-a939-0f23-5e78-6ff1e31b4a7a","name":"🛟 Error handling & retries"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🔐 Security\n\nNever trust inbound payloads: the webhook path is unguessable. Add header auth or IP allow-listing for defense in depth. Secrets live in n8n credentials — never in node parameters.","width":360,"height":260,"color":1},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[190,-500],"id":"5295ac6f-727f-5bb9-af82-c9bd90f7ed07","name":"🔐 Security"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🤖 AI cluster\n\nPurple nodes form one AI unit: the root node orchestrates, sub-nodes plug in via typed ports (model / memory / tools / parser). Swap the chat model without rewiring anything else. Costs scale with tokens — keep prompts lean and cap iterations.","width":360,"height":260,"color":6},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[610,-500],"id":"d6e4e964-96b9-5ff8-2b61-a4be57bfd710","name":"🤖 AI cluster"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🛠 Customize me\n\nQuick wins: point the data nodes at your own accounts (see 🔑 lines on each card), adjust the trigger cadence, and tune thresholds/labels to your task automation process. Every node card explains its role — safe to extend at any marked branch.","width":360,"height":260,"color":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1030,-500],"id":"da6a8fb3-2b6a-3a97-c53a-85b2c56e672f","name":"🛠 Customize me"}],"connections":{"Receive Inbound Webhook":{"main":[[{"node":"Required Fields Present?","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Required Fields Present?":{"main":[[{"node":"Detect Sentiment","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Abort — Malformed Input","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Google Gemini Chat Model":{"ai_languageModel":[[{"node":"Detect Sentiment","type":"ai_languageModel","index":0}]]},"Detect Sentiment":{"main":[[{"node":"Escalate Negative — Discord","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Log Neutral Feedback","type":"main","index":0},{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Thank the Sender","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Escalate Negative — Discord":{"main":[[{"node":"Collect All Outcomes","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Log Neutral Feedback":{"main":[[{"node":"Collect All Outcomes","type":"main","index":1}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Thank the Sender":{"main":[[{"node":"Collect All Outcomes","type":"main","index":2}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Collect All Outcomes":{"main":[[{"node":"Sort Requests Newest First","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Sort Requests Newest First":{"main":[[{"node":"Guard Non-Empty query","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Guard Non-Empty query":{"main":[[{"node":"Cap Batch Volume","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Cap Batch Volume":{"main":[[{"node":"Align Field Names","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Align Field Names":{"main":[[{"node":"Summarize Run Stats","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Summarize Run Stats":{"main":[[{"node":"Append Audit Row (Notion)","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Append Audit Row (Notion)":{"main":[[{"node":"Send Summary to Slack","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Capture Failure Context":{"main":[[{"node":"Escalate Failure to Slack","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Send Summary to Slack":{"main":[[],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]}},"active":false,"settings":{"executionOrder":"v1"},"meta":{"templateCredsSetupCompleted":false},"tags":[],"pinData":{},"versionId":"320a341c-59f0-4fa8-8396-41bb36e9c9bb","id":"FDX00887"}